h','closed','closed','','subscribe','','','2019-11-21 10:57:10','2019-11-21 10:57:10','',0,'http://dev.evantiv.com/vogue_wp/?p=45',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(46,1,'2019-11-21 10:57:10','2019-11-21 10:57:10','','Digital','','publish','closed','closed','','digital','','','2019-11-21 10:57:10','2019-11-21 10:57:10','',0,'http://dev.evantiv.com/vogue_wp/?p=46',2,'nav_menu_item','',0),(47,1,'2019-11-21 10:57:10','2019-11-21 10:57:10','','Newsletter','','publish','closed','closed','','newsletter','','','2019-11-21 10:57:10','2019-11-21 10:57:10','',0,'http://dev.evantiv.com/vogue_wp/?p=47',3,'nav_menu_item','',0),(48,1,'2019-11-22 05:36:33','2019-11-22 05:36:33','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"#\">From</a> the table of the path-breaking, award-winning playwright, Eve Ensler, comes a compelling memoir titled&nbsp;<em>No Apology</em>. Ensler spent a childhood being sexually abused and physically humiliated by her father, Arthur Ensler, while her mother watched on with a cold detachment. Ensler, who was never apologised to by her father for the years of trauma he put her through, sees&nbsp;<em>The Apology</em>&nbsp;as a harsh narrative that leads the way to a sense of healing. The Apology is written from the perspective of her sadistic father, who perpetrated a myriad of violations against her. The words she\'s has written are words that she\'s longed to hear from her father.&nbsp;<em>The Apology</em>&nbsp;also, in Ensler\'s view, sets an example and creates a manuscript of an apology for men.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Mumbai helps</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>She mentioned, that while growing up, she had this fantasy that her father will wake up, come to his senses and render her an apology last Wednesday, as Akshara Centre, One Billion Rising and Avid Learning held a book reading and discussion at the Royal Opera House, Mumbai, in an ambitious effort to shine a light upon the rising violence against women in the country (a Reuters report, in 2018, named India as one the most dangerous country for women—one rife with sexual violence).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>The Apology</em>&nbsp;is much more than that, however. The abuse Ensler was subjected is the most common form of abuse for a woman. This memoir bares the genesis Ensler’s ground-breaking episodic play,&nbsp;<em>The Vagina Monologues</em>. She faces her unflinching truth and compassion as she shares her vision for the future. Ensler has endeavoured to implement a new path for herself and a possible road (to recovery) for other abuse survivors of sexual abuse.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Rahul Bose, a prominent Indian actor, read excerpts from&nbsp;<em>The Apology</em>&nbsp;at the event. The reading eventually trailed off into a rousing conversation as the book\'s themes of abuse and atonement were touched upon by famed journalist, Faye D\'Souza.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://youtu.be/8tWGjWrVm5I\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://youtu.be/8tWGjWrVm5I\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->','Eve Ensler\'s book reading in Mumbai helps put focus on the violence against women in the country','','publish','open','open','','single-post','','','2019-11-22 10:08:41','2019-11-22 10:08:41','',0,'http://dev.evantiv.com/vogue_wp/?p=48',0,'post','',0),(49,1,'2019-11-22 05:36:33','2019-11-22 05:36:33','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Lorem Ipsum</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','retygyr','','inherit','closed','closed','','48-revision-v1','','','2019-11-22 05:36:33','2019-11-22 05:36:33','',48,'http://dev.evantiv.com/vogue_wp/2019/11/22/48-revision-v1/',0,'revision',