 chosen winners at the ceremony.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Stay tuned to this space for more details on Vogue x Nykaa: The Power List 2019, and get live updates from the night on December 9, 2019</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Also read:</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.vogue.in/fashion/content/inside-ekaya-first-ever-flagship-store-in-mumbai-kala-ghoda-palak-shah-textiles\">Ekaya is now in Mumbai: Here\'s everything we know</a></em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.vogue.in/fashion/content/presenting-the-winners-vogue-women-of-the-year-2019\">Presenting the winners: Vogue Women Of The Year 2019</a></em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://www.vogue.in/news/content/janhvi-kapoor-reveals-alternative-career-choice-bollywood-confessions-video#intcid=recommendations_default-similar2_ea386acb-7b8f-49c1-96f1-3233fb28b607_text2vec1_text2VecSimilarity\">This is what Janhvi Kapoor would be doing if she hadn\'t become an actor</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','You can choose the winners of Vogue x Nykaa: The Power List 2019 yourself','','inherit','closed','closed','','104-revision-v1','','','2019-11-26 06:04:24','2019-11-26 06:04:24','',104,'http://dev.evantiv.com/vogue_wp/2019/11/26/104-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(108,1,'2019-11-26 06:25:32','2019-11-26 06:25:32','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Crafted with signature detailing, it’s safe to say that&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.vogue.in/topics/anita-dongre/\">Anita Dongre</a>’s offerings are easily recognisable. The couturier launched her label in 2013, and her designs have gained a prime spot in most celebrity wardrobes since then. Her sharara sets in particular are favourites among the stars—with everyone from&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.vogue.in/topics/alia-bhatt/\">Alia Bhatt</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.vogue.in/topics/sonakshi-sinha/\">Sonakshi Sinha</a>&nbsp;to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.vogue.in/topics/priyanka-chopra/\">Priyanka Chopra</a>&nbsp;being spotted in them over the years—and there’s something for every sensibility in her roster. Intricate embroidery, quirky details, fun prints—she does it all with equal ease.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Alia Bhatt is a sworn patron—she looked towards various iterations of Anita Dongre’s sharara sets during the promotions for&nbsp;<em>Kalank</em>&nbsp;(2019). The actor made a strong case for the ethnic staple’s versatility with her choices, wearing everything from a black sharara set featuring a full-sleeved kurta to an ivory number that came with a strappy romantic kurta. On the other hand,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.vogue.in/topics/katrina-kaif/\">Katrina Kaif</a>&nbsp;highlighted her penchant for brightly coloured sharara sets with intricate floral embroidery in two standout looks. She wore a sunshine yellow sharara set with pink, orange and red blooms for a Ganesh puja, and went with a pretty coral number with white floral embroidery for Eid celebrations.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you prefer something more traditional, take notes from Priyanka Chopra, who stepped out in an emerald green sharara set by Anita Dongre while promoting&nbsp;<em>The Sky Is Pink</em>&nbsp;(2019). Or do like Sonakshi Sinha and go down the printed route—the star’s&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.vogue.in/vogue-closet/collection/sonakshi-sinha-printed-kurta-sharara-dupatta-silver-jhumkas-ring-juttis-sunglasses/\">blue and white sharara set</a>&nbsp;stood out for its busy, romantic print. Scroll ahead for our edit of all the times Bollywood celebrities stepped out in Anita Dongre’s sharara sets.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','All the times Bollywood celebrities were spotted in sharara sets by Anita Dongre','','publish','open','open','','all-the-times-bollywood-celebrities-were-spotted-in-sharara