y&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.vogue.in/how-to/content/how-to-take-care-of-leather-bags-and-shoes-in-the-monsoons\">leather bags</a>. But Swarang Designs makes it look like they were a match made in design heaven. Launched in 2016, Swati Wadhwa’s brand of homegrown leather goods is on a mission to revive India’s forgotten crafts, one beautiful collection at a time. They have explored Madhubani painting from Bihar, Dhokra metal casting from Chhattisgarh, Chindi dhurrie making from Panipat, and Jhabua beadwork from Madhya Pradesh so far, using the techniques on a variety of handmade bags, including styles like barrel and saddle bags, boxy slings, foldable totes and wrap wallets. Additionally, they also offer quirky accessories like key chains, card holders and laptop sleeves in genuine leather.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Grain</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->','3 accessory brands you need to know about to shop leather responsibly','','publish','open','open','','3-accessory-brands-you-need-to-know-about-to-shop-leather-responsibly','','','2019-11-26 06:32:03','2019-11-26 06:32:03','',0,'http://dev.evantiv.com/vogue_wp/?p=112',0,'post','',0),(113,1,'2019-11-26 06:31:16','2019-11-26 06:31:16','','f-5.1','','inherit','open','closed','','f-5-1','','','2019-11-26 06:31:16','2019-11-26 06:31:16','',112,'http://dev.evantiv.com/vogue_wp/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/f-5.1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(114,1,'2019-11-26 06:32:01','2019-11-26 06:32:01','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Regional painting, local metal work and handwoven dhurrie bits aren’t techniques one expects to find on contemporary&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.vogue.in/how-to/content/how-to-take-care-of-leather-bags-and-shoes-in-the-monsoons\">leather bags</a>. But Swarang Designs makes it look like they were a match made in design heaven. Launched in 2016, Swati Wadhwa’s brand of homegrown leather goods is on a mission to revive India’s forgotten crafts, one beautiful collection at a time. The