&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.vogue.in/content/amrapali-jewels\">Amrapali Jewels</a>. She wore a similar sari in yellow for Deepika Padukone and Ranveer Singh’s reception as well, amping it up with yet another styling hack. This time, she kept all the focus on her embellished blouse by draping the pallu like a dupatta from the back. We also saw her in a cobalt blue sari, worn with a matching sleeveless blouse, statement jhumkas and bedazzled juttis.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Over the years, Janhvi Kapoor has experimented with all versions of the traditional drape, from chiffon saris to classic silk numbers. She paired a gold and pink Manish Malhotra sari with a contrasting mint green and gold blouse for a special dinner hosted by President Ram Nath Kovind in 2018, and was spotted in a lightweight chiffon white sari by the same designer just last month. Floral saris are another favourite with the star. Cases in point: that peach Anita Dongre sari she was seen in earlier this year, which came covered with yellow blooms; and her ivory Tarun Tahiliani drape, featuring a pretty floral border in shades of maroon, purple and green and worn with a strappy floral blouse. Looking to upgrade your ethnic wardrobe with a classic drape? Scroll ahead to bookmark your favourites from Janhvi Kapoor’s sari collection.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:core-embed/instagram {\"url\":\"https://www.instagram.com/p/Bwe5t91A5Nv/?utm_source=ig_embed\",\"type\":\"rich\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"instagram\",\"className\":\"\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-instagram wp-block-embed is-type-rich is-provider-instagram\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://www.instagram.com/p/Bwe5t91A5Nv/?utm_source=ig_embed\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/instagram -->','Janhvi Kapoor’s sari collection will inspire you to add the six yard staple to your own wardrobe','','publish','open','open','','janhvi-kapoors-sari-collection-will-inspire-you-to-add-the-