eek quality and authenticity. Puja studied biochemistry, however she discovered her creative side in New York, while she was pursuing a Master’s in Genetics at the New York University (NYU). The creative bug in her soon took over and she gave up her NYU program to pursue Jewelry Design at the Fashion Institute of Technology (FIT), New York’s premier design school.\r\n\r\nAn avid art lover, Puja was actively associated with New York’s finest museums – the Metropolitan Museum and the Brooklyn Museum of Art. These affiliations have a vivid influence on Puja’s creations as she employs her design sensibility and exposure to the world’s best art in her jewellery. Puja moved back to India in 2002 and launched her jewellery design studio in 2003 for bespoke jewellery. Aurus represents the next step in her journey from running a design studio to setting up a boutique jewellery store.','Aurus','','publish','closed','closed','','aurus','','','2019-12-04 05:33:54','2019-12-04 05:33:54','',0,'http://dev.evantiv.com/vogue_wp/?post_type=portfolios&#038;p=277',0,'portfolios','',0),(278,1,'2019-12-02 05:44:52','2019-12-02 05:44:52','SPECIALITIES : BRIDAL, BRIDAL CONSULTING, CUSTOMISATION, ACCESSORIES, JEWELLERY, ONLINE\r\n\r\nBrainchild of designer Puja Shah, Aurus Jewels is a young brand that creates exquisite jewellery. The brand creates a design sensibility within a boutique set-up, which makes your jewellery-buying experience very personal. Aurus combines simplicity with elegance to design jewellery that’s classic and timeless. With uncompromising standards of craftsmanship, the use of the finest jewels and a founding philosophy of the highest ethical standards, Aurus caters clients that seek quality and authenticity. Puja studied biochemistry, however she discovered her creative side in New York, while she was pursuing a Master’s in Genetics at the New York University (NYU). The creative bug in her soon took over and she gave up her NYU program to pursue Jewelry Design at the Fashion Institute of Technology (FIT), New York’s premier design school.\r\n\r\nAn avid art lover, Puja was actively associated with New York’s finest museums – the Metropolitan Museum and the Brooklyn Museum of Art. These affiliations have a vivid influence on Puja’s creations as she employs her design sensibility and exposure to the world’s best art in her jewellery. Puja moved back to India in 2002 and launched her jewellery design studio in 2003 for bespoke jewellery. Aurus represents the next step in her journey from running a design studio to setting up a boutique jewellery store.','Aurus','','inherit','closed','closed','','277-revision-v1','','','2019-12-02 05:44:52','2019-12-02 05:44:52','',277,'http://dev.evantiv.com/vogue_wp/277-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(279,1,'2019-12-02 05:48:01','2019-12-02 05:48:01','<strong>YEAR STARTED : 2015</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>SPECIALITIES : FLOWERS, GIFT BOXES, ONLINE</strong>\r\n\r\nWorking with fresh and long-lasting flowers, One Roze is a luxury floral atelier, specializing in fresh Ecuadorian preserved roses and unique fresh floral arrangements. The label was founded in 2015 by Keerthi Reddy Kumbam.\r\n\r\nPartners Keerthi Kumbam and Shruthi Malhan were overly fascinated with flowers since a young age. Noticing a huge gap in the market for floral gifting options available in our country Apart from the usual alternatives included the traditional dozen red roses that were being sold everywhere inspired Keerthi to launch the brand ‘ONE ROZE’.\r\n\r\nAn alien concept, the idea of the long-lasting roses (Roses that last for 1-5 years) was something very new. However, with the amazing feedback  that they received they have been able to expand and open at UB city mall, Bangalore.\r\n\r\nOne Roze offers exclusive floral decor services for weddings and other celebratory events. The brand has also recently introduced fresh and preserved bridal bouquets, tiaras and head pieces, which can be customised per the theme.\r\n\r\nThey presently deliver fresh flowers  in Parisian hatboxes, luxury hampers and crates for personal and corporate gifting in Hyderabad and Bangalore and the preserved long-lasting flowers are shipped nationwide.','One Roze','','publish','closed','closed','','one-roze','','','2019-12-04 05:34:57','2019-12-04 05:34:57','',0,'http://dev.evantiv.com/vogue_wp/?post_type=portfolios&#038;p=279',0,'portfolios','',0),(280,1,'2019-12-02 05:48:01','2019-12-02 05:48:01','YEAR STARTED : 2015\r\n\r\nSPECIALITIES : FLOWERS, GIFT BOXES, ONLINE\r\n\r\nWorking with fresh and long-lasting flowers, One Roze is a luxury floral atelier, specializing in fresh Ecuadorian preserved roses and unique fresh floral arrangements. The label was founded in 2015 by Keerthi Reddy Kumbam.\r\n\r\nPartners Keerthi Kumbam and Shruthi Malhan were overly fascinated with flowers since a young age. Noticing a huge gap in the market for floral gifting options available in our country Apart from the usual alternatives included the traditional dozen red roses that were being sold everywhere inspired Keerthi to launch the brand ‘ONE ROZE’.\r\n\r\nAn alien concept, the idea of the long-lasting roses (Roses that last for 1-5 years) was something very new. However, with the amazing feedback  that they received they have been able to expand and open at UB city mall, Bangalore.\r\n\r\nOne Roze offers exclusive floral decor services for weddings and other celebratory events. The brand has also recently introduced fresh and preserved bridal bouquets, tiaras and head pieces, which can be customised per the theme.\r\n\r\nThey presently deliver fresh flowers  in Parisian hatboxes, luxury hampers and crates for personal and corporate gifting in Hyderabad and Bangalore and the preserved long-lasting flowers are shipped nationwide.','One Roze','','inherit','closed','closed','','279-revision-v1','','','2019-12-02 05:48:01','2019-12-02 05:48:01','',279,'http://dev.evantiv.com/vogue_wp/279-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(281,1,'2019-12-02 05:49:18','2019-12-02 05:49:18','<strong>YEAR STARTED : 2011</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>SPECIALITIES : WOMENSWEAR, READY TO WEAR, ONLINE</strong>\r\n\r\nAn Indian collective, SCHÖN is a rapidly growing young label which was launched in 2011 by Sakshee Pradhan. The label specialises in womenswear that encapsulates feminine beauty through its unique style and silhouettes and hails inspiration from the classic era - 1920s to 1950s. Focusing on combining elegance of the colonial era with the edgy modernism of today is what describes SCHÖN in the perfect sense. With a focus on fashion for the modern woman, it marries fashion with practicality in easy silhouettes.\r\n\r\nSCHÖN pronounced as \'she-own’, is a German word that translates to beautiful. The founder and creative head, Sakshee Pradhan is a graduate from The National Institute of Fashion Technology. Having attended workshops and student exchange programs in New York and London, Sakshee has worked with veteran Indian couture designers and is also a proud and active member of the Fashion Design Council of India (FDCI).\r\n\r\nWorking to perfection, the label takes pride in its quality and service and has a loyal clientele not only India, but also in the Middle East (Jeddah, Riyadh & Kuwait), London, Australia (Sydney) & South Africa and tries to bring something refreshing to the table with each of its collections!','Schön by Sakshee Pradhan','','publish','closed','closed','','schon-by-sakshee-pradhan','','','2019-12-04 05:35:22','2019-12-04 05:35:22','',0,'http://dev.evantiv.com/vogue_wp/?post_type=portfolios&#038;p=281',0,'portfolios','',0),(282,1,'2019-12-02 05:49:18','2019-12-02 05:49:18','YEAR STARTED : 2011\r\n\r\nSPECIALITIES : WOMENSWEAR, READY TO WEAR, ONLINE\r\n\r\nAn Indian collective, SCHÖN is a rapidly growing young label which was launched in 2011 by Sakshee Pradhan. The label specialises in womenswear that encapsulates feminine beauty through its unique style and silhouettes and hails inspirat