6,'http://dev.evantiv.com/vogue_wp/266-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(304,1,'2019-12-04 05:31:38','2019-12-04 05:31:38','<strong>YEAR STARTED : 2012</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>SPECIALITIES : WOMENSWEAR, TROUSSEAU, COUTURE</strong>\r\n\r\n431-88 was started to design a line for the woman who embraces her sexiness with an allusion of a sporty style. Minimal in its outlook, the label exhibits a sharp focus on deconstructing the idea behind its absolute core and translating that into astute designs and detailed tailoring. In every piece, traditional seams and darts are manipulated to achieve a constrained distortion. The label has been by worn by fashion A-listers such as Alia Bhatt, Deepika Padukone, Jacqueline Fernandez, Nargis Fakhri, Athiya Shetty and Sonakshi Sinha amongst others. The designer, Shweta Kapur is a design graduate from London College of Fashion, and has worked with VPL in New York, Burberry in London and trained with Abu Jani Sandeep Khosla and Jaanvi in India. She has been showing her collection at the Amazon Fashion Week ever since. She has also been featured in many magazines as one of the upcoming young designers in India.','431-88 By Shweta Kapur','','inherit','closed','closed','','266-revision-v1','','','2019-12-04 05:31:38','2019-12-04 05:31:38','',266,'http://dev.evantiv.com/vogue_wp/266-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(305,1,'2019-12-04 05:32:37','2019-12-04 05:32:37','<strong>YEAR STARTED : 2017</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>SPECIALITIES : WOMENSWEAR, TROUSSEAU, BRIDAL, ONLINE, READY TO WEAR</strong>\r\n\r\nA mélange of classic crisp cuts and Indian handloom, this elegant luxurious label, is inspired by the old world regalia of Rajasthan in India. Conceptualised and created by the sister-duo Sweta Agrawal and Pallavi Podar, the brand truly reflects the designers and curator\'s innate style and aesthetics. While Sweta can be described by her rich Rajasthani inheritance and her passion to design clothes that appeals to confident strong women, Pallavi caters to the uniqueness and out-of-the-box style of the brand.\r\nAt an opportune time in November 2017, the designers decided to finally convert their passion into a full fledge career and the brand\'s maiden Khadi collection was born.\r\nHand spun and woven, the brand\'s taste in clothing is classic with clean and modern sensibilities in monotones, cutting across the borders and corners of the world. The brand\'s Enchanted Khadi Collection is an expression of true spirit, being a perfect blend of pure natural, soothing fabric with organza and sparkling embellishments. The silhouettes encompass a range of styles from fitted jackets, pants, dresses and co-ords.','A Humming Way','','inherit','closed','closed','','268-revision-v1','','','2019-12-04 05:32:37','2019-12-04 05:32:37','',268,'http://dev.evantiv.com/vogue_wp/268-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(306,1,'2019-12-04 05:32:53','2019-12-04 05:32:53','<strong>YEAR STARTED : 2016</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>SPECIALITIES : WOMENSWEAR, CUSTOMISATION, READY TO WEAR, ONLINE</strong>\r\n\r\nFounded and spearheaded by Mrs Vina Ahuja along with their effervescent creative person Sanjana Shetty and the uber talented Alexander Kaleekal, Akashi Clothing is a label conceptualised around the idea of Modern India. Backed with over 22 years of industry experience coupled with a professional qualification in interior design, Vina Ahuja is best known for her extensive knowledge in textiles and fashion.\r\nAkashi Clothing began its journey at the crossroads of tradition and modernity, with a strong belief in sustainability and contemporary aesthetics.\r\nBreathing life into tales of empowerment and diversity, of all sizes and shapes, from different walks of life, Akashi is looking to encourage the women of today to rediscover India with a whole new perspective. The brand creates easy wear clothing, supporting the cottage industries of India thereby encouraging the traditional techniques to be beautifully presented on contemporary silhouettes.\r\nTheir recent Wildflower collection is an ideal summer wardrobe with flowy fabrics in pastel colors paired with beautiful detailing of embroidery work.\r\nVisit to view their entire collection: https://www.akashi.in/','Akashi Clothing','','inherit','closed','closed','','270-revision-v1','','','2019-12-04 05:32:53','2019-12-04 05:32:53','',270,'http://dev.evantiv.com/vogue_wp/270-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(307,1,'2019-12-04 05:33:15','2019-12-04 05:33:15','<strong>YEAR STARTED : 2017</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>SPECIALITIES : WOMENSWEAR, TROUSSEAU, BRIDAL, READY TO WEAR, ONLINE</strong>\r\n\r\nBrainchild of designer Usha Devi, Anka is a label that seamlessly blends traditional cream and gold weaves of Kerala with a modern and contemporary feel. The brand experiments with texture and pattern to posit timelessness in a dynamic new market. Their designs embrace and reflect the raw aesthetic of their muse \'modern Kerala\' - which is serene, vibrant and has a sense of simple elegance.\r\nWith a workforce of over hundred and fifty, Anka is an endeavour to revive and sustain the weaving communities of Balaramapuram.','Anka','','inherit','closed','closed','','272-revision-v1','','','2019-12-04 05:33:15','2019-12-04 05:33:15','',272,'http://dev.evantiv.com/vogue_wp/272-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(308,1,'2019-12-04 05:33:32','2019-12-04 05:33:32','<strong>YEAR STARTED : 2017</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>SPECIALITIES : WOMENSWEAR, PRET, READY TO WEAR, ONLINE</strong>\r\n\r\nConceptualized and led by the talented husband-wife duo Vimarsh and Alpana Razdan, Attic Salt is a unique label that focuses on sustainability and keeping the local artisans’ work relevant in modern India. Backed with enormous global industry exposure, the directors can be best described as a talent powerhouse. Alpana is a management graduate and a NIFT Delhi Alumni while Vimarsh graduated from NIFT Delhi and IIM Kolkata.\r\n\r\nWith a collective 40 years of joint work experience and having worked with leading global fashion houses like Marc Jacob, DVF, Karl Lagerfeld, Paco Rabanne, etc the duo finally decided to launch their own brand with the aim of bringing the latest international fashion to the doorstep of the Indian consumer. A perfect amalgamation of local and global, Attic Salt’s creations feature beautifully handcrafted techniques blended with elegant silhouettes.\r\n\r\nThe brand’s prime objective is to make every customer feel special and they do this beautifully through their affordable luxury pieces that can transition from day-to-night with utmost ease. Their designs are currently retailed in most upscale retail outlets across metropolitans and major cities in India.','Attic Salt','','inherit','closed','closed','','274-revision-v1','','','2019-12-04 05:33:32','2019-12-04 05:33:32','',274,'http://dev.evantiv.com/vogue_wp/274-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(309,1,'2019-12-04 05:33:48','2019-12-04 05:33:48','<strong>SPECIALITIES : BRIDAL, BRIDAL CONSULTING, CUSTOMISATION, ACCESSORIES, JEWELLERY, ONLINE</strong>\r\n\r\nBrainchild of designer Puja Shah, Aurus Jewels is a young brand that creates exquisite jewellery. The brand creates a design sensibility within a boutique set-up, which makes your jewellery-buying experience very personal. Aurus combines simplicity with elegance to design jewellery that’s classic and timeless. With uncompromising standards of craftsmanship, the use of the finest jewels and a founding philosophy of the highest ethical standards, Aurus caters clients that seek quality and authenticity. Puja studied biochemistry, however she discovered her creative side in New York, while she was pursuing a Master’s in Genetics at the New York University (NYU). The creative bug in her soon took over and she gave up her NYU program to pursue Jewelry Design at the Fashion Institute of Technology (FIT), New York’s premier design school.\r\n\r\nAn avid art lover, Puja was actively associated with New York’s finest museums – the Metropolitan Museum and the Brooklyn Museum of Art. These affiliations have a vivid influence on Puja’s creations as she employs her design sensibility and exposure to the world’s best art in her jewellery. Puja moved back to India in 2002 and launched her jewellery design studio in 2003 for bespoke jewellery. Aurus represents the next step in her journey from running a design studio to setting up a boutique jewellery store.','Aurus','','inherit','closed','closed','','277-revision-v1','','','2019-12-04 05:33:48','2019-12-04 05:33:48','',277,'http://dev.evantiv.com/vogue_wp/277-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(310,1,'2019-12-04 05:34:03','2019-12-04 05:34:03','<strong>YEAR STARTED : 2018</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>SPECIALITIES : WOMENSWEAR, CUSTOMISATION, BRIDAL, COUTURE, TROUSSEAU</strong>\r\n\r\nBrainchild of designer Payal Patel and her mother Hansa Patel, Barikee is an exquisite label specializing in custom-made bridal wear. Backed by a strong cultural influence, this brand offers some of the most intricate pieces that blend native Indian traditional crafts and techniques with modern wearable silhouettes for every unique woman.\r\n\r\nThe brand was first initiated by Hansa, 7 years ago and was later joined by daughter Payal, who is a Fashion Design graduate from New York.\r\n\r\nPayal strongly believes in the importance and power of intricate detailing and this is reflected in all her unique designs. From some of the best, easy-breezy summer ensembles to bold, scene stealing bridal couture designs, Barikee’s masterpieces seamlessly guarantee to make heads turn while enhancing the confidence and individuality of the woman wearing them. Rich fabrics, tasteful colour palettes, and gorgeous embellishments come together to create one-of-a-kind constructions to make every occasion a special one.\r\n\r\nEvery outfit narrates a beautiful story of tradition, art, technique and love with a sense of freshness, keeping in mind fair trade practices for all their employees.\r\n\r\nIf you’re willing to make a strong statement and don’t want to compromise on your individuality, Barikee is where your search ends.','Barikee','','inherit','closed','closed','','287-revision-v1','','','2019-12-04 05:34:03','2019-12-04 05:34:03','',287,'http://dev.evantiv.com/vogue_wp/287-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(311,1,'2019-12-04 05:34:15','2019-12-04 05:34:15','<strong>YEAR STARTED : 2018</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>SPECIALITIES : WOMENSWEAR, MENSWEAR, CUSTOM-MADE, ONLINE, READY-TO-WEAR, OCCASION WEAR</strong>\r\n\r\nIntent on maintaining the individual style of the client, siblings Mouna Gummadi and Sahith Gummadi started their own label HILO Design in 2018. The luxury brand offers custom made designs for those looking at a complete wardrobe makeover or simply looking to create something special for a particular occasion.\r\n\r\nWith a post-graduate degree in Interior Designing from Pearl Academy, Mumbai, Mouna believes that the right colour palette and its utilisation in the right proportions will create aesthetic silhouettes. Sahith, on the other hand brings about a perfect amalgamation of technical detailing and design, giving the brand a new dimension.\r\n\r\nThis new-age luxury fashion label focuses not only on personalising the clients’ outfits but also making sure that each piece is comfortable enough for them to breeze through the day.\r\n\r\nFrom vibrant complimenting orange and blue ghaghra cholis to sky blue pant suits, HILO Design streamlines each outfit by embracing style with modern elegance. The fashion label’s versatile use of hues and its collaboration between the new with the traditional makes it perfect for men and women to appreciate vintage charm while maintaining their individuality. HILO Designs uncluttered modern silhouettes creates an air of timelessness materialising the brand’s ideas of creating chic Indo-western, modern and traditional trousseaus.','HILO Design','','inherit','closed','closed','','283-revision-v1','','','2019-12-0